#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:1
msgid "For Security"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:3
msgid "_Could an adversary breach the security of the kernel?_"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:5
msgid ""
"This is the index of the **security** guidelines. Each subsection is its own "
"page, and each entry below links a stable `short-name` to its guideline, "
"with a one-line gist so a reader (or a review tool) can grasp the guideline "
"before opening it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:10
msgid "Index"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:12
msgid "**[Memory Safety](memory-safety.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:13
msgid ""
"[`justify-unsafe-use`](memory-safety.md#justify-unsafe-use): Precede every "
"`unsafe` block with a `// SAFETY:` comment justifying soundness."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:14
msgid ""
"[`document-safety-conds`](memory-safety.md#document-safety-conds): Give "
"every `unsafe` fn/trait a `# Safety` section stating caller obligations."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:15
msgid ""
"[`deny-unsafe-kernel`](memory-safety.md#deny-unsafe-kernel): All `kernel/` "
"crates `#![deny(unsafe_code)]`; only OSTD crates may use `unsafe`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:16
msgid ""
"[`module-boundary-safety`](memory-safety.md#module-boundary-safety): An "
"`unsafe` block's soundness spans all code touching the same private state; "
"minimize that module."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:18
msgid "**[Security Properties](security-properties.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:19
msgid ""
"[`validate-at-boundaries`](security-properties.md#validate-at-boundaries): "
"Validate all user-supplied data at boundaries (e.g. syscall entry), then "
"trust it internally."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-security/index.md:21
msgid "No **path-specific** guidelines yet."
msgstr ""
